    "## 0 Install pyclmuapp\n",
    "if not install pyclmuapp"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "! pip install pyclmuapp"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1 Initialize pyclmuapp\n",
    "\n",
    "- The inputfolder, outputfolder, logfolder, and scriptfolder will be checked in the current working directory.\n",
    "- If the folder does not exist, it will be created.\n",
    "- User can specify the folders by using the inputfolder, outputfolder, logfolder, and scriptfolder parameters.\n",
    "- Inputfolder, outputfolder, logfolder, and scriptfolder parameters are optional."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Folder 'inputfolder' already exists.\n",
      "Folder 'outputfolder' already exists.\n",
      "Folder 'logfolder' already exists.\n",
      "Folder 'scriptsfolder' already exists.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pyclmuapp import pts_clmu\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "o = pts_clmu(\n",
    "    pwd=os.getcwd(),)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3 check the default case configuration and revise\n",
    "we use the single point case [***PTS model***](https://escomp.github.io/ctsm-docs/versions/master/html/users_guide/running-single-points/running-pts_mode-configurations.html) as the default case. The default case with the following configuration:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'case_name': 'Manchester',\n",
       " 'resolution': 'f09_g17',\n",
       " 'compset': '2000_DATM%CRUv7_CLM50%SP_SICE_SOCN_SROF_SGLC_SWAV',\n",
       " 'case_lat': '53.246',\n",
       " 'case_lon': '-2.5',\n",
       " 'RUN_STARTDATE': '2008-08-08',\n",
       " 'DATM_CLMNCEP_YR_START': '2008',\n",
       " 'DATM_CLMNCEP_YR_END': '2008',\n",
       " 'STOP_OPTION': 'ndays',\n",
       " 'case_length': '10',\n",
       " 'hist_avgflag_pertape': 'A',\n",
       " 'hist_nhtfrq': '-1',\n",
       " 'hist_mfilt': '240',\n",
       " 'output_murban': 'True',\n",
       " 'mu_urban': \"'TSA'\"}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "o.caseconfig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**How to revise the config?**\n",
    "\n",
    "o.caseconfig['\\*\\*'] = \"\\*\\*\"\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: all the config must be string"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'case_name': 'Manchester',\n",
       " 'resolution': 'f09_g17',\n",
       " 'compset': '2000_DATM%CRUv7_CLM50%SP_SICE_SOCN_SROF_SGLC_SWAV',\n",
       " 'case_lat': '53.246',\n",
       " 'case_lon': '-2.5',\n",
       " 'RUN_STARTDATE': '2008-08-08',\n",
       " 'DATM_CLMNCEP_YR_START': '2008',\n",
       " 'DATM_CLMNCEP_YR_END': '2008',\n",
       " 'STOP_OPTION': 'ndays',\n",
       " 'case_length': '10',\n",
       " 'hist_avgflag_pertape': 'A',\n",
       " 'hist_nhtfrq': '1',\n",
       " 'hist_mfilt': '24000',\n",
       " 'output_murban': 'False',\n",
       " 'mu_urban': \"'TSA_U'\"}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "o.caseconfig['case_length'] = \"10\"\n",
    "o.caseconfig['hist_nhtfrq'] = '1'\n",
    "o.caseconfig['hist_mfilt']='24000'\n",
    "o.caseconfig['output_murban'] = 'False' # output the whole urban area weather (if True, the output the TBD, HD and MD urban)\n",
    "o.caseconfig['mu_urban'] = \"'TSA_U'\" # output variables for the urban area\n",
    "o.caseconfig"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Change the year of the caseconfig?\n",
    "  - --> o.caseconfig['year'] = \"2009\"\n",
    "- \"output_murban\" is a required parameter, \n",
    "  - when is \"True\", the output will be saved muti-urban class.\n",
    "  - when is \"False\", the output will be saved single-urban class,and use the default output.\n",
    "- \"'mu_urban' can define other urban variables\n",
    "    refer: [output names](https://escomp.github.io/ctsm-docs/versions/release-clm5.0/html/users_guide/setting-up-and-running-a-case/master_list_file.html)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To learn more? --> [CTSM docs](https://escomp.github.io/ctsm-docs/versions/master/html/users_guide/index.html)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4 run a case with o.caseconfig\n",
    "\n",
    "the ouput file name will be return after `o.run()`\n",
    "\n",
    "***Note!***: \n",
    "PTS model using the global data to drive single point simulation, so the first time you run it, you need to download a lot of input data, which will consume a lot of time. This data is downloaded automatically according to the config. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "original = o.run(iflog=True, cmdlogfile='pts.log') # This will run the case and return the log, \n",
    "#cmdlogfile is optional to save the log, it is important to save the log for debugging\n",
    "original"
   ]

    "|ALB_ROOF_DIF|albedo of roof |unitless| radiative|\n",

    "|ALB_IMPROAD_DIF| albedo of impervious road | unitless| radiative|\n",

    "|EM_IMPROAD| albedo of impervious road | unitless| radiative|\n",

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot(ds, label=None):\n",
    "    dd = ds['TSA_U'].isel(lat=0,lon=0).groupby('time.hour')\n",
    "    mean = dd.mean('time')\n",
    "    var = dd.var('time')\n",
    "    plt.plot(mean, label=label)\n",
    "    plt.fill_between(mean['hour'].values, mean - var, mean + var, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot(ds0, label='original')\n",
    "plot(ds1, label='modified')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.xlabel('hour')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('TSA')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Results**\n",
    "\n",
    "The cases of original and modified surface albedo are shown in the figure. The modified surface albedo is 0.2 lower than the original one. The modified surface albedo leads to a lower air temperature. Espacially, the air temperature is lower in the afternoon."
   ]

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "def plot(ds, label, ax):\n",
    "    dd = ds.isel(lat=0,lon=0).groupby('time.hour')\n",
    "    mean = dd.mean('time')\n",
    "    var = dd.var('time')\n",
    "    ax.plot(mean, label=label)\n",
    "    ax.fill_between(mean['hour'].values, mean - var, mean + var, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "plot(ds0['TSA_U'], label='original', ax=axs[0])\n",
    "plot(ds1['TSA_U'], label='modified', ax=axs[0])\n",
    "plot(df['TSA_U'], label='original forcing', ax=axs[0])\n",
    "plot(dsf['TSA_U'], label='modified forcing', ax=axs[0])\n",
    "axs[0].legend()\n",
    "axs[0].set_xlabel('Hour of day')\n",
    "axs[0].set_ylabel('TSA [K]')\n",
    "\n",
    "plot(ds1['TSA_U']-ds0['TSA_U'], label='original', ax=axs[1])\n",
    "plot(dsf['TSA_U']-df['TSA_U'], label='warming 1 K', ax=axs[1])\n",
    "axs[1].legend()\n",
    "axs[1].set_xlabel('Hour of day')\n",
    "axs[1].set_ylabel('TSA difference [K]')\n",
    "plt.show()"
